"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-237-Whats-new-for-the-spatial-web","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover the latest spatial features for the web on visionOS 26. We’ll cover how to display inline 3D models with the brand new HTML model element. And we’ll share powerful features, including model lighting, interactions, and animations. Learn how to embed newly supported immersive media on your web site, such as 360-degree video and Apple Immersive Video. And get a sneak peek at adding a custom environment to your web pages."}],"type":"topic"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image"},"WWDC25-231-call-js":{"identifier":"WWDC25-231-call-js","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-231-call-js.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"davidleee.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"davidleee.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/davidleee.jpeg"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributions are welcome!"}],"title":"Contributions are welcome!","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link"},"https://github.com/davidleee":{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/davidleee","type":"link","title":"GitHub","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/davidleee","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}]},"WWDC25-231-scroll-behavior":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-231-scroll-behavior","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-231-scroll-behavior.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-256-Whats-new-in-SwiftUI":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-256-whats-new-in-swiftui","title":"What’s new in SwiftUI","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-256-Whats-new-in-SwiftUI","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn what’s new in SwiftUI to build great apps for any Apple platform. We’ll explore how to give your app a brand new look and feel with Liquid Glass. Discover how to boost performance with framework enhancements and new instruments, and integrate advanced capabilities like web content and rich text editing. We’ll also show you how SwiftUI is expanding to more places, including laying out views in three dimensions."}]},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/231":{"checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/231","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/231","type":"download"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-233-Whats-new-in-Safari-and-WebKit":{"title":"What’s new in Safari and WebKit","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-233-whats-new-in-safari-and-webkit","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-233-Whats-new-in-Safari-and-WebKit","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how the latest web technologies in Safari and WebKit can help you create incredible experiences. We’ll highlight different CSS features and how they work, including scroll driven animation, cross document view transitions, and anchor positioning. We’ll also explore new media support across audio, video, images, and icons.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-236-Unlock-GPU-computing-with-WebGPU":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-236-unlock-gpu-computing-with-webgpu","title":"Unlock GPU computing with WebGPU","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how the WebGPU API provides safe access to GPU devices for graphics and general-purpose computation. We’ll also explore the WGSL shading language to write GPU programs. And we’ll dive into best practices to achieve optimal performance while using minimal power across desktop and mobile devices."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-236-Unlock-GPU-computing-with-WebGPU","kind":"article"},"WWDC25-231-decide-policy":{"identifier":"WWDC25-231-decide-policy","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-231-decide-policy.png"}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-245-Whats-new-in-Swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-245-whats-new-in-swift","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Join us for an update on Swift. We’ll talk about workflow improvements that make you more productive, and new and modernized library APIs for fundamental programming tasks. We’ll show examples of Swift adoption throughout more layers of the software stack. Finally, we’ll explore new language features for both improving approachability of concurrency, and achieving peak performance when you need it.","type":"text"}],"title":"What’s new in Swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-245-Whats-new-in-Swift"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"image"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/webviewscrollinputbehavior(_:for:)/":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"webViewScrollInputBehavior(_:for:)"}],"type":"link","title":"webViewScrollInputBehavior(_:for:)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/webviewscrollinputbehavior(_:for:)\/","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/webviewscrollinputbehavior(_:for:)\/"},"WWDC25-231-navigation-progress-normal":{"identifier":"WWDC25-231-navigation-progress-normal","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-231-navigation-progress-normal.png"}],"alt":null}}}